<subSubSection pageId="255" pageNumber="860" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="255.[2064,2662,882,1310]" pageId="255" pageNumber="860">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[2069,2304,1040,1074]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pagensis">Maxomys pagensis</taxonomicName>
forms a clade with 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rajah">M. rajah</taxonomicName>
, with which it isa sister species, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Robinson" baseAuthorityYear="1921" box="[2069,2236,1119,1153]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="panglima">M. panglima</taxonomicName>
. It has been included as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[2213,2340,1158,1192]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surifer">M. surifer</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="255" pageNumber="860" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" startId="255.[2067,2239,1206,1231]" targetBox="[1454,2044,892,1304]" targetPageId="255">
<paragraph blockId="255.[2064,2662,882,1310]" pageId="255" pageNumber="860">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2067,2243,1206,1231]" pageId="255" pageNumber="860">Distribution.</emphasis>
Siberut, Sipora, North Pagai, and South Pagai Is (Mentawai Is), off W Sumatra.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="255" pageNumber="860" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="255.[1452,2661,1315,2175]" pageId="255" pageNumber="860">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1455,1706,1315,1349]" pageId="255" pageNumber="860">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 170-218 mm, tail 163-204 mm, ear 22-25 mm, hindfoot 41-45 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Mentawai Archipelago Spiny Rat is large, with coarse and spiny pelage. Dorsum is ocherous and nearly black along back and lighter on sides, with brown wash on outer surfaces of hindlegs. Cheeks are dirty brownish buff. Venter is pale creamy buff, although some specimens have light ocherous band around neck. Feet are whitish and slightly dark brown dorsally. Ears are rounded; vibrissae are long and black. Tail is less than 100% of headbody length and distinctly bicolored, blackish brown above and whitish below. Skull is similar to that of the Indomalayan Spiny Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Miller" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[2159,2297,1630,1664]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Maxomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="255" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surifer">M. surifer</taxonomicName>
). There are four pairs of mammae: one pectoral, one post-axillary, and one inguinal.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
